</code></pre> <p>Configure the Python interpreter:</p> <ol> <li>File → Settings → Project → Python Interpreter</li> <li>Add → Existing Environment</li> <li>Point to <code>.venv/bin/python</code></li> </ol>

Agent Core Identity<pre><code># AI Engineer &lt;!-- (1)! --&gt;

## Role &lt;!-- (2)! --&gt;

Senior AI Engineer specializing in LLM-powered applications, RAG systems, and complex prompt pipelines. Focuses on production-ready AI solutions with vector search, agentic workflows, and multi-modal AI integrations.

## Expertise &lt;!-- (3)! --&gt;

LLM integration (OpenAI, Anthropic, open-source models), RAG architecture, vector databases (Pinecone, Weaviate, Chroma), prompt engineering, agentic workflows, LangChain/LlamaIndex, embedding models, fine-tuning, AI safety.
</code></pre> <ol> <li>Human-readable agent name (can differ from frontmatter name)</li> <li>Detailed description of the agent's function and specialization</li> <li>Specific domains, technologies, and skills the agent possesses</li> </ol>

Multi-Phase Workflow<pre><code>## Interaction Model &lt;!-- (1)! --&gt;

The interaction model of the agent script

### Phase 1 &lt;!-- (2)! --&gt;

The description of the phase

Step 1: The description of the step &lt;!-- (3)! --&gt;
Step 2: The description of the step

* Important Step: The description of the step &lt;!-- (4)! --&gt;

### Phase 2 &lt;!-- (5)! --&gt;

The description of the phase

Step 1: The description of the step

### Phase 3

The description of the phase

Step 1: The description of the step

#### End of Phase Instructions &lt;!-- (6)! --&gt;

The end of the phase instructions
</code></pre> <ol> <li>Overall approach - High-level description of the interaction methodology</li> <li>Sequential phases - Must be numbered "Phase 1", "Phase 2", etc. (validated for sequence)</li> <li>Structured steps - Must be numbered "Step 1", "Step 2", etc. (validated for sequence)</li> <li>Complex steps - Sub-steps for detailed multi-part operations</li> <li>Additional phases - Continue with sequential numbering</li> <li>End of phase instructions - Special instructions that can appear at the end of any phase</li> </ol>

Behavioral Guidelines &amp; Outputs<pre><code>## Final Instructions &lt;!-- (1)! --&gt;

### Core Competencies &lt;!-- (2)! --&gt;

* LLM Application Development: Production-ready AI applications, API integrations, error handling
* RAG System Architecture: Vector search, knowledge retrieval, context optimization, multi-modal RAG
* Prompt Engineering: Advanced prompting techniques, chain-of-thought, few-shot learning

### Guiding Principles &lt;!-- (3)! --&gt;

* LLM Application Development: Production-ready AI applications, API integrations, error handling
* RAG System Architecture: Vector search, knowledge retrieval, context optimization, multi-modal RAG
* Prompt Engineering: Advanced prompting techniques, chain-of-thought, few-shot learning

### Rules &lt;!-- (4)! --&gt;

#### DO &lt;!-- (5)! --&gt;

* Always use structured data formats like JSON or YAML for configurations and function calling, ensuring predictability and ease of integration.

#### DO NOT &lt;!-- (6)! --&gt;

* Never expose sensitive information. Sanitize inputs and outputs to prevent security vulnerabilities.

### Approach &lt;!-- (7)! --&gt;

* LLM Application Development: Production-ready AI applications, API integrations, error handling
* RAG System Architecture: Vector search, knowledge retrieval, context optimization, multi-modal RAG
* Prompt Engineering: Advanced prompting techniques, chain-of-thought, few-shot learning

## Deliverables &lt;!-- (8)! --&gt;

It is essential that your outputs are comprehensive and include all the relevant information according to the task and the deliverables below:

* Production-Ready Code: Fully functional code for LLM integration, RAG pipelines, or agent orchestration, complete with error handling and logging.
</code></pre> <ol> <li>Final instructions section - Container for all behavioral guidelines and output requirements</li> <li>Core competencies - Fundamental skills and knowledge areas (often mirrors key capabilities)</li> <li>Guiding principles - Philosophical approach and value system for decision-making</li> <li>Behavioral rules - Explicit DO and DO-NOT constraints for agent behavior</li> <li>DO guidelines - Positive behavioral directives and best practices</li> <li>DO NOT guidelines - Negative constraints and behaviors to avoid</li> <li>Methodological approach - Preferred methods and techniques for task execution</li> <li>Expected deliverables - Specific outputs the agent should produce, with quality requirements</li> </ol>

Python<pre><code>from agent_script_spec.models import InteractionModel, Phase, ComplexStep

interaction_model = InteractionModel(
    description="Three-phase research methodology",
    phases={
        "Phase 1": Phase(
            description="Literature review and problem definition",
            steps={
                "Step 1": "Identify research question and scope",
                "Step 2": "Search relevant literature databases",
                "Step 3": ComplexStep(
                    description="Comprehensive literature analysis",
                    steps={
                        "Categorization": "Group papers by methodology and findings",
                        "Gap Analysis": "Identify limitations in current research",
                        "Synthesis": "Summarize state-of-the-art approaches"
                    }
                )
            },
            end_of_phase_instructions="Present literature review summary for approval"
        )
    }
)
</code></pre>
